To align a row of divs to the right using flex, we can use `justify-content` property and set it to `flex-end`. Here is an example code snippet:
	
HTML:

```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="item">Item 1</div>
  <div class="item">Item 2</div>
  <div class="item">Item 3</div>
</div>
```

CSS:

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: flex-end;
}

.item {
  width: 100px;
  height: 100px;
  background-color: red;
  margin: 5px;
}
```

In this example, we have a container div with three child divs that we want to align to the right. We set `display` property of the container to `flex` and `justify-content` property to `flex-end`. This will align all the child elements to the end (right) of the row.


You can see a live example here: https://codepen.io/nidhi_agarwal/pen/poJLzvpG
